---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>

<div class="page-container">

    <a class="back-link" href="/">
        ← Back to Home
    </a>

    <h1>About</h1>

    <hr class="experience-divider" />

    <section>

        <div class="about-intro">
        
            <div>
            
                <h3 class="company-section-title">
                    Introduction
                </h3>
                
                <p>
                    I'm Tihamér Gál. Throughout my career, I've worked 
                    on products ranging from sheet metal structures to industrial 
                    valves and pumps, and automated pool cover systems. 
                    While the products have changed, what has remained constant 
                    is my interest in understanding how things work, how they're 
                    made, and how they can be improved. To me, good engineering 
                    isn't about adding complexity — it's about creating solutions 
                    that are reliable, efficient, and practical.
                </p>

            </div>

            <img
                src="/images/about.jpg"
                alt="Portrait of Tihamér Gál"
                class="about-photo"
            />

        </div>

    </section>

    <section>

        <h3 class="company-section-title">
            My approach
        </h3>

        <p>
            Whether I'm developing a new product, improving an existing design, or 
            optimizing a process, I try to understand the bigger picture before 
            jumping into details. That approach also shapes how I work with others.
        </p>

        <p>
            I enjoy collaborating with people from different disciplines because good products 
            aren't created by engineering alone. Manufacturing, sourcing, quality, sales, and 
            customers all bring valuable perspectives that lead to better solutions. It's also why 
            I enjoy staying involved beyond the design phase. Some of the most valuable 
            lessons I've learned have come from working alongside the people who 
            manufacture, assemble, and test the products.
        </p>

        <p>
            When I have the opportunity to learn a new tool or technology that can improve my 
            work, I tend to take it. That's how I became responsible for 3D scanning at 
            Flowserve and later introduced 3D printing into my work at Dekobo.
        </p>

    </section>

    <section>

        <h3 class="company-section-title">
            Beyond Engineering
        </h3>

        <p>
            When I'm not working, you'll usually find me spending time with friends, 
            travelling, or carrying my analogue film camera in search of moments worth 
            capturing. I enjoy film photography because it encourages me to slow down 
            and appreciate the process as much as the final image.
        </p>

    <section class="about-photo-section">
    
        <img
            src="/images/dana-point.jpg"
            alt="Dana Point, California photographed on 35 mm film"
            class="about-feature-photo"
        />

        <div class="about-photo-footer">

            <div class="about-photo-caption">

                <span>
                    Dana Point, California, USA
                </span>
                
                <span class="about-photo-subcaption">
                    Shot on 35 mm film
                </span>
            </div>

            <a
                href="https://instagram.com/amil_gareth"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="about-photo-link"
            >
            View gallery →
            </a>

        </div>

    </section>

    </section>

    <section>

        <h3 class="company-section-title">
            Looking Ahead
        </h3>

        <p>
            After several years working in Hungary and Spain, I've returned to 
            Budapest and am looking for my next opportunity.
        </p>

        <p>
            I'm particularly interested in roles where I can take ownership of products, 
            continue learning, and be part of a collaborative team that values continuous improvement.
        </p>

    </section>

</div>

</Layout>